organic_results.title: Changes in college students' value patterns in the 1950's, 1960's, and 1970's
organic_results.snippet: Surveys of undergraduate men at Dartmouth in 1952, 1968, and 1974 and at the University of Michigan in 1952, 1969, and 1974 used identical items. From 1952 to 1968-69 the changes were extensive--decline in traditional religion, increase in political commitments and social criticism, decline in other-direction, and a sharp drop in anxieties about deviant groups in society.
